

1️⃣ Connect to Each App Server
You need to SSH into each app server in the Stratos Datacenter:

ssh tony@stapp01
ssh steve@stapp02
ssh banner@stapp03

2️⃣ Backup the SSH Config File
Always backup before editing critical files:

sudo cp /etc/ssh/sshd_config /etc/ssh/sshd_config.bak

3️⃣ Edit the SSH Configuration
Open the SSH config in your preferred editor:

sudo vi /etc/ssh/sshd_config

Find the line:
#PermitRootLogin yes
Change it to:
PermitRootLogin no

4️⃣ Test the SSH Configuration
Before restarting SSH, test the config to avoid locking yourself out:

sudo sshd -t

5️⃣ Restart the SSH Service
Apply the changes:

sudo systemctl restart sshd

grep PermitRootLogin /etc/ssh/sshd_config
